\title{the successor restriction of a successor algebra}
\taxon{definition}
\date{2023-10-30}
\author{jonmsterling}
\import{base-macros}
\meta{source}{\citek{joyal-moerdijk-1995}}

\import{jms-00C6}
\import{jms-00C9}

\let\T{#{T}}
\let\TT{#{\mathbb{T}}}
\let\C{#{\mathcal{C}}}
\let\X{#{X}}
\let\sX{#{s\cdot\X}}

\p{Let \TT be a monad on a category \C, and let \X be an [successor algebra](jms-00C9) for \TT. We define the \em{successor restriction} of \X to be the [\em{weak} algebra](jms-00C8) #{\sX :\equiv \suc{\X}\cdot X} defined by [restricting](jms-00CQ) \X along its successor map.}
